HEADWORD: Glyptodont
<hw>Glyp"to*dont</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld>
<def>One of a family (<fam>Glyptodontid⟦ae⟧</fam>) of extinct South
American edentates, of which Glyptodon is the type. About twenty species
are known.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

